body_html:
I kept the names of the tensors consistent from when I created the model. Is the y tensor considered as one of the input_arrays?

I don't think so. You'll have to write --input_arrays=x,y and define their shapes too.

BTW, this should be unrelated to the kPie kernel. You can replace it with the kReference for testing, but I think the issue is with the way you are populating input arrays. Maybe you can provide us with the .pb file you are using?

> I kept the names of the tensors consistent from when I created the model. Is the y tensor considered as one of the input_arrays?

I don't think so. You'll have to write --input_arrays=x,y  and define their shapes too.

BTW, this should be unrelated to the kPie kernel. You can replace it with the kReference for testing, but I think the issue is with the way you are populating input arrays.  Maybe you can provide us with the .pb file you are using?
